r an extra pop. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"peaches and cream baked oatmeal\" width=\"1739\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Peaches and Cream Baked Oatmeal.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-scaled.jpg 1739w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-728x921.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-768x971.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-1214x1536.jpg 1214w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-1619x2048.jpg 1619w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-3-1-150x190.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1739px) 100vw, 1739px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI love that this recipe holds together: you can cut actual squares of baked oatmeal and freeze them. The squares also make it easy to drizzle on cream, milk or top with more yogurt.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"peaches and cream baked oatmeal\" width=\"1672\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Peaches and Cream Baked Oatmeal.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-scaled.jpg 1672w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-728x958.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-768x1011.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-1167x1536.jpg 1167w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-1556x2048.jpg 1556w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-4-1-150x197.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1672px) 100vw, 1672px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cspan\u003eHere’s how I make it!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFirst up, the diced peaches. I leave the skin on mine because we don’t mind it (I actually like it), but feel free to peel the peaches before dicing. I can’t tell a huge difference when everything is mixed together. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThen, the dry ingredients. Oats, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"peaches and cream baked oatmeal\" width=\"1680\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Peaches and Cream Baked Oatmeal.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-scaled.jpg 1680w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-728x953.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-768x1006.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-1173x1536.jpg 1173w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-1564x2048.jpg 1564w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-7-150x196.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1680px) 100vw, 1680px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eNext, the wet ingredients. Eggs, plain greek yogurt, milk, vanilla extract and maple syrup. If you don’t want to use maple syrup, you can use honey. Or even the same amount of sugar, just put it in the dry ingredients. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFinally, the streusel. This part is definitely optional and I’ve made many baked oatmeals recipes without it. But it adds the most wonderful brown sugar crunch to the oatmeal! You mix together brown sugar, flour, butter and a pinch of cinnamon together until it becomes a sandy texture. Sprinkle it all over top and bake!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"peaches and cream baked oatmeal\" width=\"1692\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Peaches and Cream Baked Oatmeal.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-scaled.jpg 1692w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-728x947.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-768x999.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-1181x1536.jpg 1181w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-1575x2048.jpg 1575w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-10-150x195.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1692px) 100vw, 1692px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI love this recipe because you can make it ahead of time. You can serve it warm or chilled right from the fridge. It’s so easy to reheat, whether it’s single portions or the whole dish. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eIt can be the base for an oatmeal bar, where you serve different fruits, nuts, seeds and an array of nut butters for topping. Also! It can be meal-prepped for breakfast or lunch because it holds up so well. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan id=\"more-100163\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"peaches and cream baked oatmeal\" width=\"1738\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Peaches and Cream Baked Oatmeal.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-scaled.jpg 1738w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-728x922.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-768x972.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-1213x1536.jpg 1213w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-1618x2048.jpg 1618w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-14-150x190.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1738px) 100vw, 1738px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eIt’s cozy and comforting but at the same time – tastes like summer!\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"peaches and cream baked oatmeal\" width=\"1763\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Peaches and Cream Baked Oatmeal.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-scaled.jpg 1763w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-728x908.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-768x958.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-1231x1536.jpg 1231w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-1641x2048.jpg 1641w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-15-150x187.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1763px) 100vw, 1763px\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI live for peach season. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/peaches-and-cream-baked-oatmeal-17-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"pea